news.title: UK construction industry faces sharp decline amid weak orders and rising costs
news.para: There was also concern among firms about the impact of the increase in social security contributions paid by employers, the weak outlook for the economy, and geopolitical uncertainty.

news.title: Chennai: GCC to implement new C&D waste management guidelines from April 21
news.para: Residents undertaking minor home repairs or discarding broken ceramic sanitaryware such as tiles, bathtubs, and washbasins can now dispose of their waste free of charge at 15 designated locations across Chennai.

news.title: Average US rate on a 30-year mortgage dips to 6.64% for the second time in two weeks
news.para: The average rate has mostly trended lower since reaching just over 7% in mid-January. When mortgage rates decline, they boost homebuyers' purchasing power.

news.title: India’s office leasing market sees 5% growth in Q1 2025: Report
news.para: Driving this growth was the banking, financial services, and insurance (BFSI) sector, which recorded an over 100% YoY surge in leasing activity, accounting for 26% of total absorption during the quarter.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM inaugurates 800-acre Anant Nagar housing scheme in Lucknow
news.para: The 800-acre Anant Nagar project, developed with an investment of nearly Rs 7,000 crore, is strategically located near the international airport, expressway, and Lucknow Ring Road.

news.title: Bird Group’s Roseate Hotels & Resorts acquires property in UK
news.para: Bird Group executive director Gaurav Bhatia said: “We are beyond delighted to welcome Beechfield House and its exceptionally talented team into the Bird family.

news.title: Subhash Ghai sells two apartments in Mumbai for ₹11.61 crore
news.para: Ghai sold both apartments for ₹5.80 crore each, with each flat having a carpet area of 889 sq ft (82.59 sq meters) and a built-up area of 1,067 sq ft (99.14 sq meters).

news.title: Aastha Group wins The Economic Times Real Estate Award 2025 for Affordable Housing
news.para: Aastha Group received the Economic Times Real Estate Award 2025 for its affordable housing project, Aastha Valley. The project offers homes starting at ₹18 lakh and created many jobs while boosting the local economy. The group is expanding in Jamshedpur with various high-rise and commercial projects, emphasizing premium yet affordable housing.

news.title: How ADDA.io is transforming apartment management in India's top cities
news.para: In 2024, India saw the launch of over 350,000 residential units in its top 8 cities, with more than half in the luxury segment. ADDA.io is helping residential communities manage funds, comply with regulations, and ensure financial transparency. The platform is improving resident experiences and operations, offering advancements in AI and IoT integrations.

news.title: CREDAI Western UP calls for policy reforms to boost real estate growth and affordable housing
news.para: Dinesh Gupta, secretary of CREDAI Western UP, has emphasized the need for policy interventions to streamline real estate development in the region. He highlighted the rising demand for luxury housing, the impact of escalating land costs, and the shift towards larger residential units.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas gets NCLT’s nod to acquire Vadraj Cement for ₹1,800 crore
news.para: The resolution plan includes an upfront payment of ₹1,800 crore. Nuvoco intends to fund the transaction without a significant rise in its consolidated debt levels.

news.title: UltraTech Cement to acquire Wonder Cement's subsidiary for ₹235 crore
news.para: UltraTech Cement has executed a share purchase agreement with the existing shareholders of Wonder WallCare.

news.title: Dhruv Agarwala to step down as REA India's CEO
news.para: Dhruv Agarwala will remain with the business to support the appointment of his successor and ensure a leadership transition before departing. A comprehensive process to appoint a new CEO is underway.

news.title: Pinjore: 13 years on, 24 houses for poor remain unallotted
news.para: These vacant 411-sq ft houses, accompanied with a community centre, park, and temple, have in fact started to crumble. Over these years, govt after govt passed, but the facility, which could have been utilised by the homeless, continues to lie unused.

news.title: Delhi: Signature View Apartment residents protest as DDA delays promised rent on flat vacating
news.para: "Despite vacating their homes long ago, owners of 111 flats are yet to receive the agreed-upon rent, as the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has failed to take possession of the properties," Amrinder Singh Rakesh, president of Signature View Apartment RWA said.

news.title: Mumbai: New India Cooperative Bank's ex-chairman, wife now proclaimed offenders
news.para: The same magistrate's court has also allowed the police to attach 21 properties, including a Rs 150-crore Slum Rehabilitation Project, worth Rs 167.85 crore of five accused in the case, marking the first such action in the city after the new criminal laws came into force.

news.title: Toronto home sales fall  2.4% in March amid trade uncertainty: TRREB data
news.para: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Wednesday that he would impose a 10% baseline tariff on all imports to the United States, deepening a trade war that could upend Canada's economy.

news.title: Dusit International to expand its presence in India with 10 more hotels
news.para: The company has inked three key properties in Karnataka, which include the wellness-focused Devarana Sakleshpur, set to open in 2028, and two upcoming Dusit Princess Hotels & Resorts.

news.title: RealPage sues California city officials over rental algorithm ban
news.para: Texas-based RealPage said Berkeley's ordinance, which goes into effect this month violates the company's free speech rights and is the result of an "intentional campaign of misinformation and often-repeated false claims" about its products.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body achieves Rs 150 crore property tax target
news.para: Despite senior deputy mayor Rakesh Prashar's repeated requests for the state govt to release the remaining share of the goods and services tax (GST), the funds have not been disbursed.
